[Course_Description]
Employees want to know that their information is protected throughout their tenure at a company. Privacy professionals play a crucial role in helping organizations dutifully protect and maintain this data. In this course, Mike Chapple delves into the various restrictions on workplace privacy in the United States, as covered by the fourth domain of the IAPP Certified Information Privacy Professional/US (CIPP/US) exam. Mike goes over the federal agencies involved in the regulation of workplace privacy, as well as the different antidiscrimination laws that protect the privacy rights of employees in the workplace. He also covers employee background screening, employee monitoring, conducting misconduct investigations, and terminating employees. After wrapping up this course, you'll be prepared to answer questions from the Workplace Privacy domain of the CIPP/US exam.